, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":14,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Cecily Rumilly was born about 1092, in Skipton, Yorkshire, England as the daughter of Robert FitzRainfred de Rumilly. She married William le Meschin about 1110. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 3 daughters. She died before 1155, in Bordeaux, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France."},"et":{"about 1092–before 1155":"umbes 1092–enne 1155","1092–1112":"1092–1112","1092–1155":"1092–1155","1078–1135":"1078–1135","1115–1187":"1115–1187","1116–1187":"1116–1187","1126–1214":"1126–1214","–Male":"Surnud","1070–1096":"1070–1096","about 1092":"umbes 1092","before 1155":"enne 1155","1187":"1187","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1092":"1092","1106":"1106","1116":"1116","1126":"1126","1214":"1214","1115":"1115","1135":"1135","about 1116":"umbes 1116","1112":"1112","1155":"1155","1078":"1078","about 1115":"umbes 1115","about 1110":"umbes 1110","Skipton, Yorkshire, England":"Skipton, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gernon Castle, Normandie, Bordeaux, Aquitaine, France":"Bordeaux, Gironde, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Harringworth, Northamptonshire, England":"Harringworth, Northamptonshire, England","Cumberland, England":"Cumberland, England"},"fi":{"about 1092–before 1155":"noin 1092–ennen vuotta 1155","1092–1112":"1092–1112","1092–1155":"1092–1155","1078–1135":"1078–1135","1115–1187":"1115–1187","1116–1187":"1116–1187","1126–1214":"1126–1214","–Male":"Kuollut","1070–1096":"1070–1096","about 1092":"noi